entries.title: Biden Administration to Ask Congress to Approve of F-16 Sale to Turkey
entries.description: The $20 billion sale is contingent on Ankara’s approval of NATO expansion, administration officials said, and comes alongside a sale of F-35s to Greece.

entries.title: Seoul Crowd-Crush Probe Faults Officials, Recommends Prosecution in Itaewon Deaths
entries.description: South Korea investigators blamed local police, the district government and emergency responders

entries.title: The War in Ukraine Will Be Long. Is the West Ready?
entries.description: Time could be on Russia’s side if the U.S. and its allies don’t adjust to a prolonged conflict.

entries.title: Moscow Says It Has Seized Ukrainian Town of Soledar
entries.description: Ukrainian officials say battles are continuing for control of the eastern town.

entries.title: China's Shortage of Antivirals Puts Vulnerable People at Risk
entries.description: China is struggling with shortages of lifesaving antivirals more than a month after its government made an abrupt U-turn on its zero-Covid policies.

entries.title: South Korean President Takes Aim at North Korea, U.S. With Nuclear Comments
entries.description: For years, most of the fiery rhetoric has been coming from North Korea. Now it’s coming from Seoul.

entries.title: Meeting Between Biden, Kishida to Focus on Boosting Security Cooperation
entries.description: The two leaders will discuss countering China’s military buildup, with semiconductors and electric-vehicle subsidies likely the on agenda.

entries.title: China's Export Decline Deepens, Threatening Growth
entries.description: The export boom that carried China’s economy through much of the Covid-19 pandemic has lost momentum, adding urgency for Beijing to seek growth drivers elsewhere as the global economy struggles.

entries.title: Shinzo Abe Assassination Suspect Is Charged With Murder
entries.description: The charges against Tetsuya Yamagami in the former Japanese prime minister’s killing were delayed for months while authorities conducted a psychiatric assessment that ultimately found he was fit to stand trial.
